description.p: A set of grammars differing only in whitespace and comments, and a set of inputs differing mostly in size.
The goal is to try to measure the cost of increased input size.
Note: There are two distinct sets of grammars and inputs here: in this one, each grammar or input is double the size of its predecessor, and in the other each stop grows tenfold.
Every grammar is a variation on "S = 'a'*."
Every positive input consists of zero or more occurrences of 'a'; each negative input adds a 'b'.
